}</code>  <code><div class="col-sm-3 col-md-2 sidebar slider"> 
    <h5 style="font-family: Helvetica; text-transform: uppercase">Releases</h5>
</div></code>    You are hammering a screw! It isn't meant for being nailed, but it gets the job done. But not as well as a nail would.  Transitions were designed for this, and not animations. Animations are meant to animate the element. Transitions are meant for smoothly transition between states.  Besides, this is so much shorter!   As an optimization, I would use margins instead.  Like the following:    <code>.sidebar {
